                           DESCRiPTiON 

 Profile of the Coronation Street actress, who died on October 15. The         
 programme charts her life both before and after setting foot on the           
 Weatherfield cobbles in the role of Betty Turpin in 1969. The actress talks   
 about her difficult years as a child star, how she worked in feature films and
 radio shows, and the break-up of her marriage. With contributions by past and 
 present Corrie stars, including William Roache, Julie Goodyear, Helen Worth,  
 Sue Nicholls and Antony Cotton, as well as impresario Bill Kenwright, who     
 played Betty's son Gordon in the long-running series.
